      "title": "动词重叠 — Verb Reduplication",
      "explanation": "In Chinese, many verbs can be repeated (reduplicated) to soften a request or indicate the action is brief, casual, or just a try. Structure: Verb + Verb (e.g., 想想 - think about, 看看 - have a look, 等等 - wait a moment). For two-syllable verbs: ABAB (e.g., 考虑考虑). Reduplication makes the request less demanding. 一(yī) can be inserted: 想一想 = 想想.",
